<subsubsection xml:id="subsubsec-mode-grouped" xmlns:xi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XInclude">
    <title>Mode (Grouped)</title>
    <objectives component="outcomes">
        <introduction xml:id="auto_exnowohv">
            <dl>
                <li xml:id="auto_o24rahgd">
                    <title>Strand</title>
                    <p xml:id="auto_wzi3pz0y">
                        3.0 Statistics and Probability
                    </p>
                </li>
                <li xml:id="auto_urohusyj">
                    <title>Sub-Strand</title>
                    <p xml:id="auto_l99ohtbo">
                        3.1 Statistics 1
                    </p>
                </li>
                <li xml:id="auto_r410hf6x">
                    <title>Specific Learning Outcomes</title>
                    <p xml:id="auto_fmml3ael">
                        Determine mean, mode and median of grouped and ungrouped data
                    </p>
                </li>
                <li xml:id="auto_5ahxxkli" component="lesson-plan">
                    <title>Grade Level</title>
                    <p xml:id="auto_1zrfdv92">
                        10
                    </p>
                </li>
                <li xml:id="auto_5ofr2765" component="lesson-plan">
                    <title>Estimated Duration</title>
                    <p xml:id="auto_m3azqvl0">
                        40 minutes
                    </p>
                </li>
            </dl>
            <p xml:id="auto_7w9mpn8a" component="lesson-plan">
                <p xml:id="auto_jqnoeuzy"> Upon completion of this lesson, learners will be able to:
                <ol>
                    <li xml:id="auto_8fp736ev">
                        <p xml:id="auto_s3cjq506">
                            <alert>Know (Conceptual Understanding):</alert> Understand that the modal class is the class interval with the highest frequency in grouped data.
                        </p>
                    </li>
                    <li xml:id="auto_zjbieall">
                        <p xml:id="auto_4238kowz">
                            <alert>Do (Procedural Skill):</alert> Identify the modal class from a grouped frequency distribution table.
                        </p>
                    </li>
                    <li xml:id="auto_cgl0jao3">
                        <p xml:id="auto_wr82yjag">
                            <alert>Apply (Application/Problem-Solving):</alert> Use the modal class to make practical decisions such as inventory planning and resource allocation.
                        </p>
                    </li>
                </ol>
                </p>
            </p>
        </introduction>
    </objectives>
    <axiom component="resources">
        <!-- Link to blurb -->
        <xi:include href="../../resources-blurb-lesson.ptx" />

        <sbsgroup widths="45% 45%" margins="2% 2%">
            <sidebyside>
                <p xml:id="auto_pei07vx8">
                    <dataurl source="lesson_plans/statistics-and-probability/statistics-1/mode-grouped.pdf"> Lesson Plan </dataurl>
                </p>
                <p xml:id="auto_h0og67fp">
                    <dataurl source="lesson_plans/statistics-and-probability/statistics-1/step-by-step-guide_mode-grouped.pdf"> Step-by-Step Guide </dataurl>
                </p>
            </sidebyside>
        </sbsgroup>
    </axiom>

    <xi:include href="../../resources-materials.ptx" />

    <introduction xml:id="auto_sisk2au9">
        <p xml:id="auto_b43z1jhz">
            In grouped data, we cannot easily identify the specific number that appears most often. Instead, we identify the group that contains the most data points.
        </p>
    </introduction>

    <axiom component="lesson-plan">
        <title>Problem-Solving and Discovery</title>
        <dl>
            <li xml:id="auto_0f70cuzf">
                <title>Suggested Time</title>
                <p xml:id="auto_poq4spgd">15 minutes</p>
            </li>
            <li xml:id="auto_t2d3x6gj">
                <title>Objective</title>
                <p xml:id="auto_7h4qhxos">Students work in groups to discover the concept of modal class by identifying the interval with the highest frequency.</p>
            </li>
        </dl>
        <paragraphs>
            <title>Discussion Prompts</title>
            <ul>
                <li xml:id="auto_ul9776p2"><p xml:id="auto_n4i0ceci">Look at the Frequency column. Which number is the largest?</p></li>
                <li xml:id="auto_9zrv7iv3"><p xml:id="auto_50ku9d25">Which interval (pocket money range) has that highest frequency?</p></li>
                <li xml:id="auto_xjjs874k"><p xml:id="auto_0nv7erjl">What does this tell us about pocket money in this group?</p></li>
                <li xml:id="auto_4c2xg2m7"><p xml:id="auto_6q6kq2cz">Can we say a specific amount is the mode? Why or why not?</p></li>
            </ul>
        </paragraphs>
    </axiom>

    <activity xml:id="auto_iltm4lbs">
        <p xml:id="auto_8fshr0ee">
            <term>Work in groups</term>
        </p>
        <p xml:id="auto_940ucrf0">
            Review the pocket money distribution table below:
        </p>
        <table xml:id="auto_awpbw68f">
            <title>Pocket Money Distribution</title>
            <tabular left="medium" right="medium" top="medium" bottom="medium">
                <row halign="left" header="yes">
                    <cell>Pocket Money (Ksh)</cell>
                    <cell><m>100 - 199</m></cell>
                    <cell><m>200 - 299</m></cell>
                    <cell><m>300 - 399</m></cell>
                    <cell><m>400 - 499</m></cell>
                    <cell><m>500 - 599</m></cell>
                </row>
                <row halign="left" header="yes"> 
                    <cell>Frequency</cell>
                    <cell><m>8</m></cell>
                    <cell><m>15</m></cell>
                    <cell><m>22</m></cell>
                    <cell><m>20</m></cell>
                    <cell><m>10</m></cell>
                </row>
            </tabular>
        </table>
        <p xml:id="auto_eva0j6oy">
            <ol>
                <li xml:id="auto_tx7vitbq">
                    <p xml:id="auto_migz6bro">
                        Which group has the highest number of students?
                    </p>
                </li>
                <li xml:id="auto_uuahs7du">
                    <p xml:id="auto_zsooea1g">
                        What is the modal class of pocket money given to students?
                    </p>
                </li>
            </ol>
        </p>
    </activity>

    <axiom component="lesson-plan">
        <title>Structured Instruction</title>
        <p xml:id="auto_rx2tom1n">
            <dl>
            <li xml:id="auto_aywxy7h4">
                <title>Suggested Time</title>
                <p xml:id="auto_0bdxp9vf">10 minutes</p>
            </li>
            <li xml:id="auto_2ig9lp7t">
                <title>Objective</title>
                <p xml:id="auto_b3u65s2m">To formalize the concept of modal class, including how to identify it and the difference between ungrouped mode and grouped modal class.</p>
            </li>
            </dl>
        </p>
    </axiom>

    <insight xml:id="auto_sdbd37ew">
        <p xml:id="auto_c655yd91">
            <term>Modal Class</term>
        </p>
        <p xml:id="auto_k3sucggo">
            For grouped data, the <term>Modal Class</term> is simply the class interval with the highest frequency. It represents the range where the majority or the highest density of the data points lie.
        </p>
    </insight>


    <axiom component="lesson-plan">
        <title>Practice and Application</title>
        <p xml:id="auto_nrqhkla1">
            <dl>
            <li xml:id="auto_57ckrn0n">
                <title>Suggested Time</title>
                <p xml:id="auto_2zetk412">15 minutes</p>
            </li>
            <li xml:id="auto_310ftoe7">
                <title>Objective</title>
                <p xml:id="auto_tj66p31w">To apply the concept of modal class to identify the most common interval in grouped frequency tables.</p>
            </li>
            <li xml:id="auto_xgupmpkp">
                <title>Teacher's Role</title>
                <p xml:id="auto_dbfcp233">Work through examples with learners step by step. Circulate during independent practice and provide assistance where needed.</p>
            </li>
            </dl>
        </p>
    </axiom>

    <example xml:id="auto_m07dxhm3">
        <statement>
            <p xml:id="auto_aomqlme5">
                A company records the monthly salaries (in KES) of employees. Identify the modal class from the table below.
            </p>
            <table xml:id="auto_wof8fz9j">
                <title>Employee Salaries</title>
                <tabular left="medium" right="medium" top="medium" bottom="medium">
                    <row halign="left" header="yes">
                        <cell>Salary Range(KES)</cell>
                        <cell>Number of Employees</cell>
                    </row>
                    <row><cell><m>20,000 - 29,999</m></cell><cell><m>3</m></cell></row>
                    <row><cell><m>30,000 - 39,999</m></cell><cell><m>5</m></cell></row>
                    <row><cell><m>40,000 - 49,999</m></cell><cell><m>7</m></cell></row>
                    <row><cell><m>50,000 - 59,999</m></cell><cell><m>10</m></cell></row>
                    <row><cell><m>60,000 - 69,999</m></cell><cell><m>9</m></cell></row>
                    <row><cell><m>70,000 - 79,999</m></cell><cell><m>6</m></cell></row>
                    <row><cell><m>80,000 - 89,999</m></cell><cell><m>5</m></cell></row>
                </tabular>
            </table>
        </statement>
        <solution>
            <p xml:id="auto_3dt73g4l">
                To find the modal class, we look for the highest frequency in the "Number of Employees" column.
            </p>
            <p xml:id="auto_28fhu2ok">
                The highest frequency is <m>10</m>. This corresponds to the salary range <m>50,000 - 59,999</m>.
            </p>
            <p xml:id="auto_947rawwr">
                Therefore, the Modal Class is <m>50,000 - 59,999</m> KES.
            </p>
        </solution>
    </example>

    <example xml:id="auto_iji716t2">
        <statement>
            <p xml:id="auto_e656njyd">
                The scores of 50 students in a statistics test are summarized below:
            </p>
            <tabular top="medium" bottom="medium" left="medium" right="medium">
                <row header="yes">
                    <cell>Class Interval</cell>
                    <cell>Frequency (f)</cell>
                </row>
                <row>
                    <cell><m>0-9</m></cell>
                    <cell><m>2</m></cell>
                </row>
                <row>
                    <cell><m>10-19</m></cell>
                    <cell><m>5</m></cell>
                </row>
                <row>
                    <cell><m>20-29</m></cell>
                    <cell><m>8</m></cell>
                </row>
                <row>
                    <cell><m>30-39</m></cell>
                    <cell><m>12</m></cell>
                </row>
                <row>
                    <cell><m>40-49</m></cell>
                    <cell><m>11</m></cell>
                </row>
                <row>
                    <cell><m>50-59</m></cell>
                    <cell><m>7</m></cell>
                </row>
                <row>
                    <cell><m>60-69</m></cell>
                    <cell><m>5</m></cell>
                </row>
            </tabular>
            <p xml:id="auto_d1bmjodw">
                Find the modal score.
            </p>
        </statement>
        <solution>
            <p xml:id="auto_4rx9vtej">
                <ol marker="(Step 1:)">
                    <li xml:id="auto_89tvivwe">
                        <p xml:id="auto_gpemgn04">
                            <term>Identify the modal class</term>
                        </p>
                        <p xml:id="auto_6gjd9t1v">
                            The modal class is the class with the highest frequency. From the table, the highest frequency is <m>12</m>, which corresponds to <m>30-39</m>.So, modal class is <m>30-39</m>.
                        </p>
                    </li>
                    <li xml:id="auto_yqlwoceb">
                        <p xml:id="auto_j82bzoe5">
                            <term>Apply the mode formula for grouped data</term>
                        </p>
                        <p xml:id="auto_ikan0n09">
                            <md>
                                <mrow> Mode = \amp L + \left( \frac {f_1 - f_0}{2 \times f_1 - f_0 - f_2} \right) \times h </mrow>
                                <mrow> = \amp 29.5 + \frac{12 - 8}{2 \times 12 - 8 - 11} \times 10</mrow>
                                <mrow> = \amp 29.5 + \frac{4}{5} \times 10</mrow>
                                <mrow> = \amp 37.8</mrow>
                            </md>
                            
                        </p>
                        <p xml:id="auto_g37haw1o">
                            Modal score <m> = 37.5</m> units
                        </p>
                    </li>
                </ol>
            </p>
        </solution>
    </example>

    <axiom component="lesson-plan">
        <title>Assessment</title>
        <p xml:id="auto_7pve57py">
            <dl>
            <li xml:id="auto_wbuvsljo">
                <title>Objective</title>
                <p xml:id="auto_tjzvafi8">To formatively assess individual learner understanding.</p>
            </li>
            <li xml:id="auto_ha6tc5h6">
                <title>Learning Experience</title>
                <p xml:id="auto_iwrlrla1">Learners independently complete a short assessment task (select from the exercises below).</p>
            </li>
            <li xml:id="auto_zw1sqeuf">
                <title>Teacher's Role</title>
                <p xml:id="auto_hb2r8tzj">Collect and review the exit tickets to gauge learner understanding and identify any common misconceptions that need to be addressed in the next lesson.</p>
            </li>
            </dl>
        </p>
    </axiom>

    <xi:include href="../../resources-checkpoint.ptx" />

    <exercise  label="ex-finding-mean-median-and-modal-class-for-grouped-data">
        <stack label="stk-finding-mean-median-and-modal-class-for-grouped-data" source="stack/top/3-0-Statistics-Probability/Statistics-1/3-1-3-Measures-of-Central-Tendency/3-1-3-2-Grouped-Data-for-Measures-of-Central-Tendency/Finding-mean,-median-and-modal-class-for-grouped-data.xml" />
    </exercise>  

    <exercise  label="ex-constructing-frequency-tables-and-calculating-mean-and-median">
        <stack label="stk-constructing-frequency-tables-and-calculating-mean-and-median" source="stack/top/3-0-Statistics-Probability/Statistics-1/3-1-3-Measures-of-Central-Tendency/3-1-3-2-Grouped-Data-for-Measures-of-Central-Tendency/Constructing-frequency-tables-and-calculating-mean-and-median.xml" />
    </exercise>

    <exercises xml:id="exercises-mode-grouped">
        <exercise xml:id="auto_bidtszf6">
            <statement>
                <p xml:id="auto_q4brslvn">
                    A Bata shop in Mombasa recorded the sizes of shoes sold during a "Back to School" sale.
                </p>
                <table xml:id="auto_6mfhsqi6">
                    <title>Shoe Sizes Sold</title>
                    <tabular halign="center" top="medium" bottom="medium" left="medium" right="medium">
                        <row header="yes">
                            <cell>Shoe Size</cell>
                            <cell>Pairs Sold</cell>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                            <cell><m>2 - 4</m></cell>
                            <cell><m>15</m></cell>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                            <cell><m>5 - 7</m></cell>
                            <cell><m>45</m></cell>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                            <cell><m>8 - 10</m></cell>
                            <cell><m>30</m></cell>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                            <cell><m>11 - 13</m></cell>
                            <cell><m>10</m></cell>
                        </row>
                    </tabular>
                </table>
                <p xml:id="auto_cs08vlnf">
                    Identify the modal class of the shoe sizes.
                </p>
            </statement>
            <answer>
                <p xml:id="auto_eqoyua4i">
                    The modal class is <m>5 - 7</m>.
                </p>
                <p xml:id="auto_ry71qatg">
                    This is because it has the highest frequency of <m>45</m> pairs sold.
                </p>
            </answer>
        </exercise>

        <exercise xml:id="auto_6w5c89a0">
            <statement>
                <p xml:id="auto_9mf8edfd">
                    The meteorological department recorded the daily rainfall (in mm) in Nyeri for the month of April.
                </p>
                <table xml:id="auto_wf8gioqg">
                    <title>Daily Rainfall</title>
                    <tabular halign="center" top="medium" bottom="medium" left="medium" right="medium">
                        <row header="yes">
                            <cell>Rainfall (mm)</cell>
                            <cell>No. of Days</cell>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                            <cell><m>0 - 4</m></cell>
                            <cell><m>10</m></cell>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                            <cell><m>5 - 9</m></cell>
                            <cell><m>4</m></cell>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                            <cell><m>10 - 14</m></cell>
                            <cell><m>12</m></cell>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                            <cell><m>15 - 19</m></cell>
                            <cell><m>3</m></cell>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                            <cell><m>20 - 24</m></cell>
                            <cell><m>1</m></cell>
                        </row>
                    </tabular>
                </table>
                <p xml:id="auto_k237h2ou">
                    State the modal class for the rainfall.
                </p>
            </statement>
            <answer>
                <p xml:id="auto_bakbre8f">
                    The modal class is <m>10 - 14</m> mm.
                </p>
                <p xml:id="auto_7dyomqrt">
                    Although <m>0 - 4</m> is high, <m>10 - 14</m> has the highest frequency of <m>12</m> days.
                </p>
            </answer>
        </exercise>

        <exercise xml:id="auto_lr8f5hss">
            <statement>
                <p xml:id="auto_3f04fpzm">
                    A speed camera on the Thika Superhighway recorded the speeds (in km/h) of <m>100</m> vehicles passing a specific point.
                </p>
                <table xml:id="auto_ny3qhw08">
                    <title>Vehicle Speeds</title>
                    <tabular halign="center" top="medium" bottom="medium" left="medium" right="medium">
                        <row header="yes">
                            <cell>Speed (km/h)</cell>
                            <cell>No. of Vehicles</cell>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                            <cell><m>60 - 79</m></cell>
                            <cell><m>15</m></cell>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                            <cell><m>80 - 99</m></cell>
                            <cell><m>55</m></cell>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                            <cell><m>100 - 119</m></cell>
                            <cell><m>25</m></cell>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                            <cell><m>120 - 139</m></cell>
                            <cell><m>5</m></cell>
                        </row>
                    </tabular>
                </table>
                <p xml:id="auto_jobv3mws">
                    Find the modal class of the vehicle speeds.
                </p>
            </statement>
            <answer>
                <p xml:id="auto_he18wyyu">
                    The modal class is <m>80 - 99</m> km/h.
                </p>
                <p xml:id="auto_hvlfycl7">
                    This interval contains the highest number of vehicles (<m>55</m>).
                </p>
            </answer>
        </exercise>

        <exercise xml:id="auto_8tq5vbye">
            <statement>
                <p xml:id="auto_wtv94w1v">
                    A survey among teenagers in a Nairobi estate showed their weekly mobile data usage (in MBs).
                </p>
                <table xml:id="auto_psoybrh2">
                    <title>Data Usage</title>
                    <tabular halign="center" top="medium" bottom="medium" left="medium" right="medium">
                        <row header="yes">
                            <cell>Data (MB)</cell>
                            <cell>No. of Teenagers</cell>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                            <cell><m>0 - 499</m></cell>
                            <cell><m>8</m></cell>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                            <cell><m>500 - 999</m></cell>
                            <cell><m>22</m></cell>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                            <cell><m>1000 - 1499</m></cell>
                            <cell><m>14</m></cell>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                            <cell><m>1500 - 1999</m></cell>
                            <cell><m>6</m></cell>
                        </row>
                    </tabular>
                </table>
                <p xml:id="auto_091p4ws2">
                    What is the modal class for the data usage?
                </p>
            </statement>
            <answer>
                <p xml:id="auto_x2hev0pg">
                    The modal class is <m>500 - 999</m> MB.
                </p>
                <p xml:id="auto_kzmn8v22">
                    This group has the highest frequency of <m>22</m> teenagers.
                </p>
            </answer>
        </exercise>
    </exercises>

    <axiom component="lesson-plan">
        <title>Differentiation</title>

        <table xml:id="auto_x3ea77yu">
            <title>Differentiation</title>
            <tabular halign="left">
                <row header="yes" bottom="minor">
                    <cell>Learner Group</cell>
                    <cell>Strategy &amp; Learning Experience</cell>
                    <cell></cell>
                </row>
                <row>
                    <cell>Struggling Learners (Support)</cell>
                    <cell>
                        <line><alert>Scaffolding:</alert> Provide highlighters to mark the highest frequency in the table. Use colour coding: highlight frequency column in one colour, modal class in another. Start with smaller tables (3–4 intervals) to build confidence. Create visual charts or bar graphs to make the modal class obvious. Provide sentence frames: <q>The highest frequency is _____. This corresponds to the interval _____.</q> Work in pairs with peer support.</line>
                    </cell>
                    <cell></cell>
                </row>
                <row>
                    <cell>On-Level Learners (Core)</cell>
                    <cell>
                        <line>The core lesson activities as described above.</line>
                    </cell>
                    <cell></cell>
                </row>
                <row>
                    <cell>Advanced Learners (Challenge)</cell>
                    <cell>
                        <line><alert>Extended Learning Experience:</alert> Explore bimodal and multimodal distributions — what causes them? Compare modal class with mean and median for the same dataset — when do they differ? Investigate datasets where modal class is NOT the best measure of central tendency. Draw histograms to visualise modal class and discuss distribution shapes. Analyse what happens to modal class when class widths change.</line>
                    </cell>
                    <cell></cell>
                </row>
            </tabular>
        </table>
    </axiom>
    <xi:include href="../../resources-assessment.ptx" />
